1
00:00:20,645 --> 00:00:21,521
(We're dating.)

2
00:00:25,108 --> 00:00:26,943
(We're in a relationship.)

3
00:00:31,573 --> 00:00:33,616
Were you feeling unwell this morning?

4
00:00:36,036 --> 00:00:36,619
Huh?

5
00:00:37,829 --> 00:00:38,913
What about Saebyeok?
[*"Morning" sounds similar to "Saebyeok" in Korean]

6
00:00:40,123 --> 00:00:40,749
Huh?

7
00:00:44,210 --> 00:00:45,879
I'm just asking if you felt unwell.

8
00:00:48,465 --> 00:00:49,591
Oh, you said morning.

9
00:00:50,133 --> 00:00:53,094
You're fine. Don't worry.

10
00:00:54,179 --> 00:00:56,306
(Dummy: Are you feeling okay?)
(Dummy: Photo)
(Dummy: Let's come here together)
Did you eat on time?

11
00:00:56,890 --> 00:00:59,851
you feel unwell,
please let me know at any time.

12
00:01:02,562 --> 00:01:05,523
WeTV Original Series

13
00:01:07,192 --> 00:01:09,402
Gi Haneul
Hwang Junsu

14
00:01:12,781 --> 00:01:14,074
Co-produced by YYDS Entertainment

15
00:01:15,617 --> 00:01:18,703
Yeo Saebaek
Lee Jawoon

16
00:01:25,043 --> 00:01:27,754
Yoon Junghan
Oh Jaehyeong

17
00:01:29,047 --> 00:01:30,882
Seri
Park Eunjo

18
00:01:36,054 --> 00:01:41,518
= Never Forget Your Enemy =

19
00:01:44,104 --> 00:01:48,566
=Episode 2=
(Back to the Future)

20
00:01:51,528 --> 00:01:55,073
The brain MRI
and neurological tests came out normal.

21
00:01:55,907 --> 00:01:58,868
Currently, it appears
to be dissociative amnesia.

22
00:02:00,745 --> 00:02:01,412
Dissociative...

23
00:02:02,372 --> 00:02:03,039
What's that?

24
00:02:03,957 --> 00:02:07,377
Patients usually experience
significant stress or trauma.

25
00:02:07,919 --> 00:02:09,838
To protect themselves,

26
00:02:10,130 --> 00:02:11,631
the brain blocks memories for now.

27
00:02:12,715 --> 00:02:15,385
Your last memory is
from when you were 19, right?

28
00:02:16,177 --> 00:02:16,636
Yes.

29
00:02:17,846 --> 00:02:19,305
That year, when I was 19,
at the school gate

30
00:02:19,806 --> 00:02:20,473
I intended to meet...

31
00:02:22,267 --> 00:02:23,810
a friend...

32
00:02:24,269 --> 00:02:25,854
Then I had an accident there.

33
00:02:26,688 --> 00:02:28,064
When I woke up

34
00:02:28,648 --> 00:02:29,858
I was in this hospital.

35
00:02:30,567 --> 00:02:33,069
Will his memory come back?

36
00:02:35,864 --> 00:02:37,532
If he tries
to force himself to remember,

37
00:02:37,866 --> 00:02:39,868
it could actually worsen his anxiety.

38
00:02:40,076 --> 00:02:43,872
It's best to recover slowly
in a safe environment.

39
00:02:44,289 --> 00:02:45,540
How should he do that?

40
00:02:46,624 --> 00:02:48,501
Try listening to the people around him

41
00:02:48,585 --> 00:02:51,921
or looking through photos, diaries,
or notes, which should be helpful.

42
00:02:52,797 --> 00:02:53,923
In this process,

43
00:02:54,340 --> 00:02:56,593
your memories will gradually return.

44
00:02:57,010 --> 00:02:57,594
You might also

45
00:02:58,178 --> 00:03:00,722
start over.

46
00:03:01,681 --> 00:03:03,850
Could it be that I deliberately want

47
00:03:04,392 --> 00:03:05,226
to forget?

48
00:03:06,436 --> 00:03:07,353
That's also possible.

49
00:03:08,229 --> 00:03:10,481
If it's a memory you couldn't bear,

50
00:03:10,940 --> 00:03:13,902
your brain naturally chooses
to forget it.

51
00:03:15,028 --> 00:03:15,987
What's important is

52
00:03:16,404 --> 00:03:18,072
whether intentional or not,

53
00:03:18,406 --> 00:03:20,074
to recover your memories safely.

54
00:03:25,496 --> 00:03:27,040
When will Saebyeok come here?

55
00:03:27,999 --> 00:03:29,667
He knows how to get here.

56
00:03:29,751 --> 00:03:30,627
Why will he come?

57
00:03:31,419 --> 00:03:31,961
What's wrong?

58
00:03:32,212 --> 00:03:33,421
Can't he come?

59
00:03:33,880 --> 00:03:35,715
Saebyeok personally arranged this room.

60
00:03:35,882 --> 00:03:37,133
He can even kick you out.

61
00:03:38,718 --> 00:03:39,969
He arranged it?

62
00:03:41,763 --> 00:03:44,182
Saebyeok was right there
when you got hurt.

63
00:03:44,724 --> 00:03:46,768
He took care of everything
before he left.

64
00:03:46,893 --> 00:03:47,894
I want to change rooms.

65
00:03:48,269 --> 00:03:49,896
Why? This room is fine.

66
00:03:50,396 --> 00:03:52,440
Anyway, there are no empty rooms.

67
00:03:52,941 --> 00:03:53,733
So annoying.

68
00:03:54,275 --> 00:03:55,443
Mom.

69
00:03:55,443 --> 00:03:56,611
Ah, it’s there.

70
00:04:00,573 --> 00:04:02,116
CG – Saebaek text message window: ‘Did you eat breakfast?’

71
00:04:07,205 --> 00:04:07,705
Haneul.

72
00:04:08,414 --> 00:04:09,415
Are you okay?

73
00:04:09,707 --> 00:04:11,584
Who are you?

74
00:04:12,710 --> 00:04:14,295
Junghan, what are you doing here?

75
00:04:14,462 --> 00:04:16,464
Of course, I came to see Haneul.

76
00:04:17,799 --> 00:04:19,926
Do you work at Saetbyeol's coffee shop?

77
00:04:20,134 --> 00:04:21,719
Hello, it's been a while.

78
00:04:22,428 --> 00:04:23,638
Well...

79
00:04:24,138 --> 00:04:25,181
How do you know me?

80
00:04:26,516 --> 00:04:28,351
Iced mint tea, with an espresso shot.

81
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:29,936
What?

82
00:04:30,645 --> 00:04:32,438
You come every day
before work to order one.

83
00:04:35,900 --> 00:04:38,194
Junghan is practically
your personal barista.

84
00:04:38,945 --> 00:04:39,487
What?

85
00:04:41,281 --> 00:04:42,448
You really don't remember?

86
00:04:44,033 --> 00:04:44,742
Sorry.

87
00:04:45,326 --> 00:04:46,369
No need to say sorry.

88
00:04:46,786 --> 00:04:48,871
Just remember me from now on.

89
00:04:51,207 --> 00:04:52,083
Wow.

90
00:04:52,709 --> 00:04:54,627
It's rare to see someone
as likable as you.

91
00:04:55,420 --> 00:04:56,212
Exactly.

92
00:04:56,713 --> 00:04:58,673
Thank you for coming to see Haneul.

93
00:04:58,673 --> 00:05:00,425
Not at all. It's what I should do.

94
00:05:02,385 --> 00:05:04,304
Luckily, your injuries aren't serious.

95
00:05:06,764 --> 00:05:07,307
Right.

96
00:05:07,890 --> 00:05:08,349
anyway

97
00:05:09,892 --> 00:05:11,144
Be more careful next time.

98
00:05:12,603 --> 00:05:13,896
Or you might be in danger again.

99
00:05:16,149 --> 00:05:17,025
Exactly.

100
00:05:17,734 --> 00:05:19,402
This is already fortunate.

101
00:05:20,403 --> 00:05:21,362
It's truly fortunate.

102
00:05:21,988 --> 00:05:23,614
- Thank you for coming.
- Thanks.

103
00:05:29,162 --> 00:05:30,288
(If you try to recover your memories,)

104
00:05:30,955 --> 00:05:32,165
(you might feel scared.)

105
00:05:35,460 --> 00:05:37,003
(But if you don't,)

106
00:05:38,755 --> 00:05:42,592
(you might lose those memories forever.)

107
00:06:07,408 --> 00:06:08,993
Can I really be discharged?

108
00:06:10,328 --> 00:06:12,080
The doctor said you're already fine.

109
00:06:12,497 --> 00:06:13,581
Didn't you see the results?

110
00:06:14,624 --> 00:06:15,583
I'm not okay.

111
00:06:16,167 --> 00:06:17,960
Half my life is gone.

112
00:06:18,294 --> 00:06:19,587
You are now

113
00:06:19,837 --> 00:06:21,756
like an empty shell.

114
00:06:24,384 --> 00:06:25,343
Saetbyeol.

115
00:06:25,676 --> 00:06:26,761
How did you get so old?

116
00:06:27,303 --> 00:06:29,389
You weren't this old in college.

117
00:06:29,764 --> 00:06:30,556
Do you want to die?

118
00:06:31,516 --> 00:06:32,433
Shut up, both of you!

119
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:33,893
She started it.

120
00:06:37,188 --> 00:06:38,314
Saebyeok's here.

121
00:06:39,065 --> 00:06:41,734
He looks good,
no matter how sloppy he is.

122
00:06:41,734 --> 00:06:42,652
Hello.

123
00:06:43,027 --> 00:06:45,613
- Did you come straight after work?
- Yes.

124
00:06:46,197 --> 00:06:48,616
Give it to me. I'll take it.

125
00:06:48,991 --> 00:06:49,742
Who are you?

126
00:06:50,701 --> 00:06:52,453
I've finished all discharge paperwork.

127
00:06:52,578 --> 00:06:53,413
Let go.

128
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:54,539
Mom.

129
00:06:54,997 --> 00:06:55,998
Let's go home.

130
00:06:56,332 --> 00:06:57,959
Do you know where home is?

131
00:06:58,876 --> 00:06:59,585
Did we move?

132
00:07:00,420 --> 00:07:01,712
You moved out.

133
00:07:02,755 --> 00:07:04,340
You need to go with Saebyeok.

134
00:07:04,715 --> 00:07:05,341
Me?

135
00:07:06,551 --> 00:07:07,176
Why?

136
00:07:08,636 --> 00:07:09,429
Don't tell me

137
00:07:10,012 --> 00:07:11,055
Yeo Saebyeok and I...

138
00:07:11,055 --> 00:07:11,764
We live together.

139
00:07:13,599 --> 00:07:15,601
You've been living together
for almost four years.

140
00:07:15,726 --> 00:07:16,686
Three years and six months.

141
00:07:17,186 --> 00:07:18,312
You remember that.

142
00:07:18,312 --> 00:07:19,981
Why did I live with him?

143
00:07:20,356 --> 00:07:21,357
Did you forget?

144
00:07:21,774 --> 00:07:24,026
Back then,
you were like Romeo and Juliet.

145
00:07:24,694 --> 00:07:28,030
The doctor advised you
to be in a familiar environment.

146
00:07:28,239 --> 00:07:30,074
It means you should live as usual.

147
00:07:31,033 --> 00:07:32,326
No way! No!

148
00:07:32,618 --> 00:07:34,454
I've lost my memory.
How can I live as usual?

149
00:07:34,704 --> 00:07:35,246
No way.

150
00:07:35,496 --> 00:07:36,122
Let's go back.

151
00:07:37,039 --> 00:07:39,333
I don't want to live
under the same roof as this guy.

152
00:07:39,417 --> 00:07:39,959
Then,

153
00:07:40,376 --> 00:07:41,169
I'll move out.

154
00:07:41,878 --> 00:07:42,420
What?

155
00:07:42,628 --> 00:07:46,924
Since you don't want to see me,
I'll move out. You stay at home.

156
00:07:48,092 --> 00:07:50,136
That should help you regain your memory.

157
00:07:50,887 --> 00:07:54,182
Mom, they're going to fight again. Let's get out of here.
Okay.

158
00:07:54,348 --> 00:07:55,808
Haneul, we're heading out first.

159
00:07:55,933 --> 00:07:58,728
- We're leaving!
- Wait. Mom. Saetbyeol.

160
00:07:59,228 --> 00:07:59,854
Gi Haneul.

161
00:08:01,230 --> 00:08:01,731
What?

162
00:08:02,648 --> 00:08:02,982
Let's go.

163
00:08:03,608 --> 00:08:04,150
Go home.

164
00:08:07,987 --> 00:08:08,571
Let go.

165
00:08:09,947 --> 00:08:11,115
Why should I go with you?

166
00:08:11,616 --> 00:08:12,742
Get in the car.

167
00:08:13,242 --> 00:08:14,577
If I don't, what will you do?

168
00:08:15,453 --> 00:08:16,162
Drag me again?

169
00:08:16,662 --> 00:08:17,163
Yeah.

170
00:08:17,872 --> 00:08:19,248
You think you can do that?

171
00:08:19,832 --> 00:08:20,666
Or I carry you?

172
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:21,792
Are you crazy?

173
00:08:22,001 --> 00:08:23,586
Do you plan to sleep on the street?

174
00:08:26,005 --> 00:08:29,091
Even if you want to sleep on the street,
I won't allow it. Get in the car.

175
00:08:59,413 --> 00:09:00,206
What are you doing?

176
00:09:01,249 --> 00:09:01,749
What?

177
00:09:02,333 --> 00:09:03,501
Are you afraid I'll eat you?

178
00:09:04,252 --> 00:09:05,086
I-I'm not scared.

179
00:09:06,462 --> 00:09:07,755
I won't force you.

180
00:09:08,881 --> 00:09:09,465
To do what?

181
00:09:10,633 --> 00:09:11,259
just...

182
00:09:11,801 --> 00:09:12,343
Anything.

183
00:09:15,680 --> 00:09:16,889
What are you talking about?

184
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:20,309
Tell me.

185
00:09:20,810 --> 00:09:22,103
What have you forgotten?

186
00:09:23,563 --> 00:09:25,982
Shouldn't you ask what I remember?

187
00:09:51,549 --> 00:09:52,133
Go on in.

188
00:09:53,384 --> 00:09:54,218
Do I live here?

189
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:55,553
Your place?

190
00:09:56,053 --> 00:09:56,762
Yeah.

191
00:09:57,597 --> 00:09:58,347
And your dad?

192
00:09:59,807 --> 00:10:00,850
He's in his hometown.

193
00:10:22,330 --> 00:10:25,291
Leaving such a nice house empty,
you just crashed

194
00:10:25,708 --> 00:10:26,959
at my place all the time.

195
00:10:31,714 --> 00:10:32,506
So here

196
00:10:32,965 --> 00:10:33,883
it's just you and me

197
00:10:34,675 --> 00:10:35,509
living together?

198
00:11:02,161 --> 00:11:03,079
What is all this?

199
00:11:04,205 --> 00:11:05,039
Our home.

200
00:11:07,917 --> 00:11:10,878
I really lived like this with you?

201
00:11:11,712 --> 00:11:12,129
Yeah.

202
00:11:13,673 --> 00:11:14,340
Is this fake?

203
00:11:15,633 --> 00:11:16,342
How is it fake?

204
00:11:16,842 --> 00:11:19,220
How on earth did I end up with you?

205
00:11:27,937 --> 00:11:29,814
Did you get this back again?

206
00:11:30,815 --> 00:11:33,776
The closet's over there.
Find something to wear yourself.

207
00:11:34,402 --> 00:11:36,195
The bathroom's there. The bedroom is...

208
00:11:37,279 --> 00:11:38,197
I know.

209
00:11:38,864 --> 00:11:39,490
You remember?

210
00:11:41,909 --> 00:11:44,870
Houses all look pretty similar, right?

211
00:11:45,871 --> 00:11:46,914
Is it okay if I move out?

212
00:11:49,542 --> 00:11:50,376
You may go.

213
00:11:51,794 --> 00:11:53,045
Call me if you need anything.

214
00:11:53,713 --> 00:11:55,172
Just go.

215
00:11:55,631 --> 00:11:56,257
I'm leaving.

216
00:12:14,984 --> 00:12:16,152
Oh, my.

217
00:12:17,653 --> 00:12:18,487
Is this me?

218
00:12:32,084 --> 00:12:37,131
I look fine.

219
00:14:15,479 --> 00:14:16,564
It's so warm.

220
00:14:19,692 --> 00:14:20,943
Do you like me?

221
00:14:31,704 --> 00:14:32,997
Answer me.

222
00:14:36,500 --> 00:14:37,376
I love you.

223
00:14:44,049 --> 00:14:44,967
Yeo Saebyeok.

224
00:14:45,009 --> 00:14:45,426
Hm?

225
00:16:21,397 --> 00:16:21,814
You...

226
00:16:22,815 --> 00:16:23,691
Why are you here?

227
00:16:25,067 --> 00:16:26,276
So energetic in the morning.

228
00:16:27,194 --> 00:16:28,487
How come you're here?

229
00:16:30,990 --> 00:16:31,782
Well...

230
00:16:32,241 --> 00:16:33,075
Let's eat breakfast.

231
00:16:46,171 --> 00:16:47,006
No way.

232
00:16:48,048 --> 00:16:48,966
Just a dream, right?

233
00:16:50,801 --> 00:16:51,719
Please.

234
00:16:53,137 --> 00:16:54,513
It has to be a dream.

235
00:16:56,181 --> 00:16:56,807
Amen.

236
00:16:57,433 --> 00:16:59,977
Oh, dear God. Help me.

237
00:17:07,317 --> 00:17:10,279
Gi Haneul, come eat.

238
00:17:27,713 --> 00:17:28,672
Come sit down.

239
00:17:30,549 --> 00:17:31,425
I'm not hungry.

240
00:17:31,925 --> 00:17:32,718
You must be hungry.

241
00:17:34,136 --> 00:17:36,513
Who eats this much in the morning?

242
00:17:37,473 --> 00:17:38,057
It's indigestible.

243
00:17:38,348 --> 00:17:40,517
It's 7:30 AM. You should be hungry.

244
00:17:40,517 --> 00:17:41,226
I'm not hungry.

245
00:17:44,438 --> 00:17:45,689
The food is innocent.

246
00:17:47,566 --> 00:17:48,400
Just sit down.

247
00:17:52,112 --> 00:17:53,322
Did my mom make this?

248
00:17:53,405 --> 00:17:53,781
I made it.

249
00:17:55,115 --> 00:17:56,158
You're lying.

250
00:17:56,950 --> 00:17:58,827
I ate at your place a lot.

251
00:17:58,911 --> 00:18:00,954
I learned how to cook from your mom.

252
00:18:01,872 --> 00:18:02,956
To be frank,

253
00:18:02,998 --> 00:18:05,501
you're more like my mom's son than I am.

254
00:18:06,502 --> 00:18:07,544
She made your favorite food.

255
00:18:08,504 --> 00:18:10,964
Your mom felt more like a mom
to me than my own mom.

256
00:18:15,302 --> 00:18:16,178
Because we're family.

257
00:18:41,495 --> 00:18:42,246
Didn't you move?

258
00:18:42,913 --> 00:18:43,872
Why were you lying next to me?

259
00:18:46,750 --> 00:18:49,002
I just came back to change clothes.

260
00:18:49,628 --> 00:18:50,629
And then somehow...

261
00:18:53,382 --> 00:18:54,299
Sneaky guy.

262
00:19:04,268 --> 00:19:04,852
Aren't you leaving?

263
00:19:06,019 --> 00:19:07,020
I was just about to.

264
00:19:09,565 --> 00:19:09,982
Do you

265
00:19:10,941 --> 00:19:11,608
invest in Bitcoin?

266
00:19:14,153 --> 00:19:16,488
You're young, but living so carefree.

267
00:19:17,322 --> 00:19:18,866
You only work when you feel like it.

268
00:19:19,908 --> 00:19:20,868
I'm not young anymore.

269
00:19:22,494 --> 00:19:24,663
So you must be happy being old.

270
00:19:25,622 --> 00:19:26,957
If you're done,

271
00:19:27,624 --> 00:19:28,959
you may leave.

272
00:19:40,220 --> 00:19:40,846
Haven't left?

273
00:19:41,471 --> 00:19:42,264
I was just leaving.

274
00:19:54,735 --> 00:19:55,402
Can you just go?

275
00:19:56,236 --> 00:19:56,778
One more thing.

276
00:19:57,988 --> 00:19:58,739
What?

277
00:19:59,573 --> 00:20:00,407
A goodbye kiss.

278
00:20:02,701 --> 00:20:04,703
On three. You'd better go.

279
00:20:05,120 --> 00:20:05,829
Three.

280
00:20:06,163 --> 00:20:06,622
Two.

281
00:20:07,122 --> 00:20:08,874
- One
- I'm going.

282
00:20:30,979 --> 00:20:34,942
(Saebyeok’s love letter to Haneul)

283
00:20:38,028 --> 00:20:39,404
What is all this?

284
00:20:59,049 --> 00:21:00,717
What a sincere letter.

285
00:21:02,511 --> 00:21:04,221
Yeo Saebyeok isn't like this.

286
00:21:06,723 --> 00:21:08,725
Was I really with him?

287
00:21:16,191 --> 00:21:19,611
(It might help to meet people you knew before.)

288
00:21:21,571 --> 00:21:22,906
I've fallen for Saebyeok.

289
00:21:23,240 --> 00:21:23,991
Goodbye.

290
00:21:31,456 --> 00:21:32,374
Enjoy your meal.

291
00:21:32,666 --> 00:21:33,250
Thank you.

292
00:21:34,126 --> 00:21:35,252
Let me know if you need anything.

293
00:21:42,342 --> 00:21:43,093
Saebyeok told me.

294
00:21:43,927 --> 00:21:46,888
You lost your memory. Are you okay?

295
00:21:48,682 --> 00:21:49,308
I'm okay.

296
00:21:49,975 --> 00:21:52,269
You forgot everything after you were 19?

297
00:21:54,896 --> 00:21:55,981
But

298
00:21:56,565 --> 00:21:58,191
I still remember you two dating.

299
00:21:59,443 --> 00:22:00,444
Come on.

300
00:22:01,361 --> 00:22:03,155
That was ten years ago.

301
00:22:03,613 --> 00:22:07,034
And it was only for a week.
Does that even count?

302
00:22:08,618 --> 00:22:09,369
So,

303
00:22:10,787 --> 00:22:12,122
are you in touch with Saebyeok?

304
00:22:13,290 --> 00:22:15,083
You and I keep in touch.

305
00:22:16,084 --> 00:22:16,793
Me?

306
00:22:17,461 --> 00:22:18,920
You work at our academy.

307
00:22:22,466 --> 00:22:24,801
So what does Yeo Saebyeok do?

308
00:22:26,970 --> 00:22:30,098
You don't know?

309
00:22:32,100 --> 00:22:34,478
I guess he invests in Bitcoin.

310
00:22:38,607 --> 00:22:39,358
Bitcoin?

311
00:22:39,816 --> 00:22:43,070
He really is popular like Bitcoin.

312
00:22:44,363 --> 00:22:46,281
Seems you really didn't know.

313
00:22:47,824 --> 00:22:48,617
Wait.

314
00:22:55,499 --> 00:22:57,084
(Yeo Saebyeok – Actor Profile)

315
00:22:57,793 --> 00:22:59,294
Is Yeo Saebyeok a celebrity?

316
00:23:00,128 --> 00:23:02,839
There shouldn't be anyone
in our country who doesn't know him.

317
00:23:02,881 --> 00:23:03,465
How so?

318
00:23:03,965 --> 00:23:05,759
Yeo Saebyeok is not only handsome,

319
00:23:06,301 --> 00:23:08,178
but surprisingly,
his acting is pretty good too.

320
00:23:13,850 --> 00:23:16,812
Sung Ji-young ADR: “I’ll contact you again!” Add SFX of the café door opening and her leaving.

321
00:23:20,732 --> 00:23:21,775
Just put them here.

322
00:23:22,818 --> 00:23:23,402
Thanks.

323
00:23:29,199 --> 00:23:29,741
Saetbyeol?

324
00:23:30,117 --> 00:23:32,202
She called and said
she'll come in the afternoon.

325
00:23:32,702 --> 00:23:33,620
What a heartless boss.

326
00:23:33,912 --> 00:23:36,873
No, she is very good to me.

327
00:23:37,207 --> 00:23:38,417
Oh, Saetbyeol is good to you?

328
00:23:40,585 --> 00:23:42,295
Actually, I was a student athlete too.

329
00:23:42,796 --> 00:23:45,048
After she found out,
she seemed to treat me even better.

330
00:23:46,133 --> 00:23:47,384
A student athlete.

331
00:23:48,593 --> 00:23:50,512
You really can't remember anything?

332
00:23:51,721 --> 00:23:54,683
There are some things I can recall.

333
00:23:54,766 --> 00:23:55,725
And some things I can’t.

334
00:23:57,060 --> 00:23:58,895
You're the first guy
I know with amnesia.

335
00:23:58,979 --> 00:24:00,564
It never happened to me before.

336
00:24:01,731 --> 00:24:04,693
Isn't that how it always is in movies?
You can't recognize anyone.

337
00:24:05,318 --> 00:24:07,779
Too bad I'm not the lead
in some tragic love story.

338
00:24:08,572 --> 00:24:10,198
I remember things before I was 19.

339
00:24:11,324 --> 00:24:12,993
I've forgotten everything after 19.

340
00:24:14,327 --> 00:24:16,079
Seems you didn't forget completely.

341
00:24:17,164 --> 00:24:18,123
It's amazing.

342
00:24:18,999 --> 00:24:20,333
It's like my brain deleted it,

343
00:24:21,209 --> 00:24:23,420
but my heart still holds onto something.

344
00:24:23,837 --> 00:24:25,839
Maybe they're memories better forgotten.

345
00:24:27,549 --> 00:24:29,843
The people
I've forgotten might be hurt too.

346
00:24:31,720 --> 00:24:36,391
(From now on, I will forget you.
You forget me too. Take care.)

347
00:24:38,310 --> 00:24:39,227
I have to go.

348
00:24:40,729 --> 00:24:41,480
Right now?

349
00:24:42,147 --> 00:24:43,482
No customers, so boring.

350
00:24:44,065 --> 00:24:45,150
Can't you stay longer?

351
00:24:45,442 --> 00:24:47,152
I need to leave
before Saetbyeol arrives.

352
00:24:47,527 --> 00:24:48,278
Come tomorrow.

353
00:24:49,070 --> 00:24:49,529
Tomorrow?

354
00:24:50,697 --> 00:24:51,198
If I'm free.

355
00:24:51,573 --> 00:24:52,240
You must come.

356
00:24:53,033 --> 00:24:53,825
I'll be waiting.

357
00:24:55,202 --> 00:24:55,619
Okay.

358
00:24:56,119 --> 00:24:56,328
I'm off.

359
00:24:57,078 --> 00:24:57,787
Wait.

360
00:25:05,378 --> 00:25:06,087
Here's my number.

361
00:25:06,963 --> 00:25:08,006
Call me before you come tomorrow.

362
00:25:08,548 --> 00:25:10,133
Iced mint tea, with an espresso shot.

363
00:25:12,677 --> 00:25:13,386
See you.

364
00:26:02,060 --> 00:26:02,561
So beautiful.

365
00:26:21,997 --> 00:26:23,123
Why did he call many times?

366
00:26:24,291 --> 00:26:25,250
(Missed call: “Idiot”)

367
00:26:25,250 --> 00:26:28,086
(Incoming call: “Idiot”)

368
00:26:33,383 --> 00:26:34,217
Hello?

369
00:26:35,218 --> 00:26:35,844
Where are you?

370
00:26:37,429 --> 00:26:38,597
Why are you shouting?

371
00:26:38,847 --> 00:26:42,183
Why didn't you answer my calls?
You've got amnesia, stop running off!

372
00:26:42,392 --> 00:26:44,352
No matter where I am,
it's none of your business.

373
00:26:44,519 --> 00:26:46,479
Enough. Where are you?

374
00:26:47,397 --> 00:26:47,856
My location?

375
00:26:49,065 --> 00:26:49,649
The beach.

376
00:26:50,275 --> 00:26:50,692
Why?

377
00:26:52,027 --> 00:26:53,153
Just stay there...

378
00:26:56,990 --> 00:26:57,741
The battery's dead.

379
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:08,627
Is there a store?

380
00:27:09,669 --> 00:27:11,129
Luckily, I got a portable charger.

381
00:27:20,138 --> 00:27:20,930
Gi Haneul.

382
00:27:22,265 --> 00:27:22,807
What?

383
00:27:23,224 --> 00:27:23,808
How did you find me?

384
00:27:24,601 --> 00:27:26,728
Even with amnesia, you still came here.

385
00:27:28,938 --> 00:27:29,856
That's so you.

386
00:27:30,273 --> 00:27:31,274
What is this place?

387
00:27:32,609 --> 00:27:33,652
A place only we knew.

388
00:27:34,694 --> 00:27:35,362
Crazy.

389
00:27:36,112 --> 00:27:37,697
There are many other people here.

390
00:27:41,660 --> 00:27:42,535
Let's take a walk.

391
00:27:49,668 --> 00:27:51,628
Are you troubled about something again?

392
00:27:54,047 --> 00:27:55,298
Did I come here often?

393
00:27:57,384 --> 00:27:58,218
You used to.

394
00:28:04,349 --> 00:28:05,892
I used to think that when I grew up,

395
00:28:07,143 --> 00:28:09,521
I'd win some Olympic gold medals,

396
00:28:11,147 --> 00:28:12,816
and become a world-famous athlete.

397
00:28:14,359 --> 00:28:17,028
Then, after retiring,
I can train promising tennis players,

398
00:28:18,321 --> 00:28:20,115
and live happily

399
00:28:20,532 --> 00:28:21,866
with a lovely wife.

400
00:28:23,785 --> 00:28:26,371
I thought I'd become something brighter.

401
00:28:28,665 --> 00:28:29,416
What am I now?

402
00:28:30,125 --> 00:28:31,960
What do you think? You're Gi Haneul.

403
00:28:34,629 --> 00:28:36,131
I'm Gi Haneul, good for nothing.

404
00:28:37,465 --> 00:28:39,551
And you're the shining star.

405
00:28:50,145 --> 00:28:50,979
People often fail

406
00:28:51,646 --> 00:28:53,273
to see their own light. Right?

407
00:28:56,693 --> 00:28:59,362
I've been watching your light
for a long time.

408
00:29:01,114 --> 00:29:02,282
From closer than anyone else.

409
00:29:12,876 --> 00:29:14,085
Go out with me.

410
00:29:28,641 --> 00:29:29,851
And I'll tell you everything.

411
00:29:34,522 --> 00:29:35,315
Okay?

412
00:29:57,295 --> 00:29:59,672
Yeo Saebyeok is so annoying.

413
00:30:00,381 --> 00:30:03,718
He acts all high and mighty
because he's handsome. It's infuriating.

414
00:30:04,844 --> 00:30:05,303
Hey.

415
00:30:09,057 --> 00:30:12,018
You shifty-eyed guy, don't talk
about others behind their backs.

416
00:30:12,185 --> 00:30:14,354
Just admit you're jealous.
Don't do something shameful.

417
00:30:15,480 --> 00:30:19,025
You don't dare speak before him.
Aren't you embarrassed?

418
00:30:19,484 --> 00:30:20,944
Who do you think you are?

419
00:30:22,153 --> 00:30:23,655
You're a parasite to Yeo Saebyeok.

420
00:30:24,447 --> 00:30:25,657
That's symbiosis.

421
00:30:26,199 --> 00:30:27,534
From now on,
never mention Saebyeok's name.

422
00:30:28,326 --> 00:30:29,702
If I hear it, you're dead.

423
00:30:41,130 --> 00:30:43,466
Your mom will be home tomorrow, right?

424
00:30:46,094 --> 00:30:47,303
It's been two years.

425
00:30:52,058 --> 00:30:53,351
After you see her,

426
00:30:54,227 --> 00:30:55,186
stop complaining.

427
00:30:56,354 --> 00:30:57,939
Just enjoy the family reunion time.

428
00:30:59,399 --> 00:31:01,401
Then see her off properly.

429
00:31:02,360 --> 00:31:03,444
Don't do anything you'll regret.

430
00:31:04,904 --> 00:31:05,697
Got it?

431
00:31:06,948 --> 00:31:07,448
Pinky promise.

432
00:31:12,996 --> 00:31:14,038
Very good.
